    <string name="help_text_2">Usage:\n\n- Swipe right: Tools\n- Swipe left: Discover\n- Swipe up: List of apps\n- Swipe down: Favorite apps\n- Double-tap on an empty area: lock screen\n- Long-press on an empty area: favorite apps\n- Long-press on the settings icon: Android system settings\n- Long-press on the browser icon: open the browser in private mode\n- Long-press on the search icon: open the browser in private mode \n</string>
    <string name="help_text_3">Settings:\n\n- Select apps for the home screen\n- Select favorite apps\n- Enable icon display\n    - System icons\n    - App icons\n    - Adaptive icons\n    - Adaptive icon color\n- Configure AI link (custom AI launchable from the browser)\n- Set web search engine (URL)\n- Set weather lURL or word\n- Wallpaper (file name; if successfully loaded from the Downloads folder, the system will save it)\n- Delete saved wallpaper\n- Reset text settings to default values\n- Re-scan apps (if the app list is incorrect after an update, installation, or deletion)</string>
    <string name="help_text_1">"A simple control app for Android. It does not interact with Android’s internal system or use external access, so it is energy-efficient and fast.\n\nIt supports the display of app icons and the use of adaptive icons.\n\nIt can also use a home screen wallpaper, which can be set in the Settings tab. (You must specify the image name; the image must be in the Downloads folder.) If it can open the specified image, it will save it.\n\nThe home screen features icons for various functions: search, weather, settings, and the default Android AI app. The basic functions are displayed at the bottom: calls, messages, app list, browser, and camera. These functions launch the default Android apps.\n "</string>
    <string name="help_text_4">A new version is available for download on the website.\nLicence: GPLv3</string>
